   3.9 RIP (4/4) 
  
     n   The IP routing table is used by the
 router     when forwarding a
 packet. This constitutes     the
 actual routing function within a router.    
     n   The IP address is then looked up in the
 NIC     ARP table for the
 physical address.     
  
 

